Sentence: Nobody saw anything at the park.
Nobody : indefinite pronoun, subject of the verb "saw", indicates negation of person
saw : verb "see", past tense, active voice
anything : indefinite pronoun, direct object of the verb "saw", scope of negation
at : preposition indicating location
the : definite article, modifies "park"
park : common noun, object of the preposition "at"

Sentence: She has never been to Paris.
She : personal pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "has"
has : auxiliary verb "have", third person singular, present perfect tense
never : adverb of frequency, indicates negation of time, modifies "been"
been : past participle of verb "be", part of the present perfect construction
to : preposition indicating direction or destination
Paris : proper noun, name of a city, object of the preposition "to"

Sentence: There is nothing in the box.
There : existential subject, introduces the existence of something
is : verb "be", third person singular, present tense
nothing : indefinite pronoun, subject complement, indicates negation of thing
in : preposition indicating location
the : definite article, modifies "box"
box : common noun, object of the preposition "in"

Sentence: He went nowhere after the meeting.
He : personal pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "went"
went : verb "go", past tense, active voice
nowhere : adverb of place, indicates negation of location, modifies "went"
after : preposition indicating time sequence
the : definite article, modifies "meeting"
meeting : common noun, object of the preposition "after"

Sentence: Neither John nor Mary liked the movie.
Neither : correlative conjunction, starts the negation pair, modifies "John"
John : proper noun, first part of the compound subject
nor : correlative conjunction, second part of the negation pair, connects "John" and "Mary"
Mary : proper noun, second part of the compound subject
liked : verb "like", past tense, active voice
the : definite article, modifies "movie"
movie : common noun, direct object of the verb "liked"

Sentence: I do not know anyone here.
I : personal pronoun, first person singular, subject of the verb "do"
do : auxiliary verb, used for negation in present tense
not : adverb, indicates negation, modifies "know"
know : main verb, base form, active voice
anyone : indefinite pronoun, direct object of the verb "know", scope of negation
here : adverb of place, modifies the clause

Sentence: They said nothing about the incident.
They : personal pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "said"
said : verb "say", past tense, active voice
nothing : indefinite pronoun, direct object of the verb "said", indicates negation of thing
about : preposition indicating topic
the : definite article, modifies "incident"
incident : common noun, object of the preposition "about"

Sentence: We have neither milk nor eggs in the fridge.
We : personal pronoun, first person plural, subject of the verb "have"
have : verb "have", present tense, active voice
neither : correlative conjunction, starts the negation pair, modifies "milk"
milk : common noun, first item in the negated list
nor : correlative conjunction, second part of the negation pair
eggs : common noun, plural, second item in the negated list
in : preposition indicating location
the : definite article, modifies "fridge"
fridge : common noun, object of the preposition "in"

Sentence: Nobody called me yesterday.
Nobody : indefinite pronoun, subject of the verb "called", indicates negation of person
called : verb "call", past tense, active voice
me : personal pronoun, first person singular, indirect object of the verb "called"
yesterday : adverb of time, modifies the verb "called"

Sentence: She eats neither meat nor fish.
She : personal pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "eats"
eats : verb "eat", third person singular, present tense, active voice
neither : correlative conjunction, starts the negation pair, modifies "meat"
meat : common noun, first item in the negated list
nor : correlative conjunction, second part of the negation pair
fish : common noun, second item in the negated list

Sentence: He never listens to advice.
He : personal pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "listens"
never : adverb of frequency, indicates negation of time, modifies "listens"
listens : verb "listen", third person singular, present tense, active voice
to : preposition indicating direction of attention
advice : common noun, uncountable, object of the preposition "to"

Sentence: There was nowhere to sit in the room.
There : existential subject, introduces the situation
was : verb "be", past tense, third person singular
nowhere : adverb of place, indicates negation of location, acts as subject complement
to : particle introducing the infinitive verb
sit : verb, base form, infinitive
in : preposition indicating location
the : definite article, modifies "room"
room : common noun, object of the preposition "in"

Sentence: I found nothing useful in the report.
I : personal pronoun, first person singular, subject of the verb "found"
found : verb "find", past tense, active voice
nothing : indefinite pronoun, direct object of the verb "found", indicates negation of thing
useful : adjective, modifies "nothing"
in : preposition indicating location
the : definite article, modifies "report"
report : common noun, object of the preposition "in"

Sentence: Neither option is acceptable to the committee.
Neither : determiner, indicates negation, modifies "option"
option : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "is"
is : verb "be", third person singular, present tense
acceptable : adjective, subject complement
to : preposition indicating relation
the : definite article, modifies "committee"
committee : common noun, object of the preposition "to"

Sentence: They told us nothing about the plan.
They : personal pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "told"
told : verb "tell", past tense, active voice
us : personal pronoun, first person plural, indirect object of the verb "told"
nothing : indefinite pronoun, direct object of the verb "told", indicates negation of thing
about : preposition indicating topic
the : definite article, modifies "plan"
plan : common noun, object of the preposition "about"
